Susan Moeller

41:08.866 --> 41:14.539 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the University of Maryland --
thanks for
being here.

41:14.572 --> 41:21.346 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MOELLER: Thank you.

41:21.379 --> 41:29.287 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WOODRUFF: Now, economics
correspondent Paul
Solman spends a little time with
a former

41:29.320 --> 41:35.693 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
hedge fund trader turned social
entrepreneur,
someone who wants to turn the
table on food

41:35.727 --> 41:42.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
shortages in inner cities by
launching an
array of eateries in both
high-end and lower-income

41:42.934 --> 41:44.602 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
neighborhoods.

41:44.635 --> 41:47.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's part of our series "Making
Sense", which
airs Thursdays on the
"NewsHour".

